                        <interp inst="t18300415-256-victim2229" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-256-off1422 t18300415-256-victim2229"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , his master
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM PLANT. I am a <rs id="t18300415-256-viclabel1424" type="occupation">hosier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-256-victim2229 t18300415-256-viclabel1424"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300415-256-crimeloc1425">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-256-crimeloc1425" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-256-crimeloc1425" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-256-off1422 t18300415-256-crimeloc1425"></join>. The prisoner was in my employ rather more than two months; for three or four weeks before I gave him in charge. I observed a particular pattern silk waistcoat which he had, and I asked him if he had been helping himself to it, from my stock; he said No, Mr. 
               <persName id="t18300415-256-person2230">
                  Edward 
                  Busby
               <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2230" type="surname" value="Busby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2230" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2230" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and he had one a piece off the same silk - this was on Sunday; and the following day I looked over my stock, and missed one of these waistcoats: I kept a sharp look on him, but detected nothing else, till the night previous to my giving him into custody, when he and the apprentice got tipsy in my absence: the following day I got a friend to come, and ask for a similar waistcoat - I said to him, "Wood it is the same as you have, let the gentleman look at that:" he brought it down after some time, and in consequence of what I had heard, I gave him into custody - the officer then searched his box, and found these<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150121"></xptr>other things, which are like what I had in the shop; but they are of that general character I could not identify them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-256-person2231">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  WILLIAM VALENTINE
               <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2231" type="surname" value="WILLIAM VALENTINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2231" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2231" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent for, and searched the prisoner's box; I found these articles, which the prosecutor said he had no doubt were his - here is a pair of stockings and a pair of gaiters; these braces are quite new - this waistcoat was brought to me by the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>Mr. PLANT. I believe this waistcoat to be mine, and these braces he says he paid the apprentice for, who says he did not receive it; I have no such black stockings as these now, but I had such, and this handkerchief and drawers.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. How many pieces of silk are there of this pattern? A. I cannot tell. These stockings I have more hesitation about than the other property; I sent the person to buy goods - the prisoner did not give me a true account of that, but I ultimately got the money.</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bought the waistcoat at Mr. Webb's; the handkerchief I brought home from India.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-256-person2232">
                  JOHN 
                  RICHMOND WEBB
               <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2232" type="surname" value="RICHMOND WEBB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2232" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2232" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I cannot recognize the prisoner as purchasing any waistcoat of me, but I had this pattern in my possession; he might have bought it at some other shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-256-person2233">
                  MARY 
                  THOMAS
               <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2233" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2233" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-256-person2233" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My husband is a labourer. I have known the prisoner twelve months; I have washed these stockings for him, before he went to the prosecutor's.</p>
